2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with predicting vulnerabilities in software from a security perspective, making it relevant to the cryptography and security sub-category. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to build a support vector machine, making it relevant to the artificial intelligence sub-category. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses active learning, a subfield of machine learning, to build the support vector machine, making it relevant to the machine learning sub-category. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper deals with source code files and their review, making it relevant to the programming languages sub-category.
